ProtoResult:
. "Let $D$ be an integral domain and let $a, b \in D$. Then 
   \begin{enumerate} \item\it $a \mid b \Leftrightarrow \langle
   b \rangle \subset \langle a \rangle$. \item\it $a$ and $b$ 
   are associates $\Leftrightarrow$ $\langle b \rangle = 
   \langle a \rangle$. \item\it $a$ is a unit in $D$ 
   $\Leftrightarrow$ $\langle a \rangle = D$. \end{enumerate}"
